---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About & Methodology"
  description="AECplayground methodology: PRISMA 4-arm systematic review, 4-tier quality scheme, 10-dimension rubric, provenance philosophy, and literature grounding."
>

  <!-- Page header -->
  <div class="page-header">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl">
      <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}`}>Home</a>
        <span class="breadcrumb-sep" aria-hidden="true">›</span>
        <span class="text-slate-400" aria-current="page">About &amp; Methodology</span>
      </nav>
      <p class="section-label">Methodology</p>
      <h1 class="font-display text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-3">
        About AECplayground
      </h1>
      <p class="text-slate-400 max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
        A PRISMA-compliant systematic review of AI benchmarks for the built environment,
        with a 4-tier quality scheme, 10-dimension scoring rubric, and strict provenance gating.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 space-y-20">

    <!-- ── PRISMA 3-Arm ──────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section id="prisma">
      <p class="section-label">Search strategy</p>
      <h2 class="section-title mb-6">PRISMA 4-Arm Protocol</h2>
      <p class="prose-aec mb-8 max-w-2xl">
        The review follows an adapted
        <strong>PRISMA 2020</strong> (Page et al., 2021) flow with four parallel search arms,
        ensuring comprehensive coverage beyond what any single database provides.
      </p>

      <!-- 4-arm visual -->
      <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 mb-10">
        {[
          {
            arm: 'A',
            title: 'Academic Database Search',
            desc: 'Systematic queries across ACM Digital Library, IEEE Xplore, arXiv, Semantic Scholar, and Scopus with AEC × benchmark × AI/LLM/VLM terms.',
            color: 'border-primary-800/60 bg-primary-950/30',
            dot:  'bg-primary-500',
          },
          {
            arm: 'B',
            title: 'OpenConstruction Snowball',
            desc: 'Domain-specific sweep via OpenConstruction.ai and related AEC AI registries, grey-literature repositories (HuggingFace Datasets, GitHub), and AEC-focused workshop proceedings not indexed by Arm A databases.',
            color: 'border-accent-800/40 bg-slate-900/40',
            dot:  'bg-accent-500',
          },
          {
            arm: 'C',
            title: 'Targeted New Search',
            desc: 'Late-stage targeted search (2026-06-21) that surfaced records not found in Arms A or B. Added R030 (CEQuest), R031 (BIM-Edit), R033 (Construction Safety Poster Benchmark); R032 found but excluded (VERIFIER F-054).',
            color: 'border-slate-700 bg-slate-900/40',
            dot:  'bg-slate-400',
          },
          {
            arm: 'D',
            title: 'VERIFIER Forward-Search',
            desc: 'VERIFIER 0.5.33 forward-search pass (2026-06-23) targeting AEC AI benchmark preprints from arXiv 2025-09 through 2026-06. Added R035 (Qwen-BIM), R036 (Ishigaki-IDS-Bench), R037 (Blueprint-Bench), R039 (BEMEval-Doc2Schema); R038 excluded as EX-CONSOL dup-of-R008.',
            color: 'border-violet-800/40 bg-violet-950/20',
            dot:  'bg-violet-400',
          },
        ].map(arm => (
          <div class={`rounded-2xl border p-6 ${arm.color}`}>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <span class={`h-2 w-2 rounded-full ${arm.dot}`}></span>
              <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-widest">Arm {arm.arm}</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-base font-display font-semibold text-white mb-2">{arm.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 leading-relaxed">{arm.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <!-- PRISMA funnel -->
      <div class="rounded-2xl bg-slate-900/50 border border-slate-800 p-6">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-300 mb-4">Screening Flow</h3>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-2 max-w-xl">
          {[
            { stage: 'Identified',         n: '162', note: 'Four arms combined (A 33 + B 118 + C 6 + D 5), 13 dups removed → 149 screened',  bar: '100' },
            { stage: 'Screened',           n: '149', note: 'Title/abstract screen (AEC-relevance + benchmark criteria)',                          bar: '92'  },
            { stage: 'Full-text reviewed', n:  '32', note: 'Eligibility assessment: must be a published AEC FM-eval benchmark',                   bar: '20'  },
            { stage: 'Included',           n:  '24', note: 'Passed rubric scoring; 8 excluded (incl. R032 F-054, R038 EX-CONSOL dup-of-R008)',   bar: '15'  },
          ].map(s => (
            <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
              <div class="w-32 shrink-0 text-right text-[11px] text-slate-500">{s.stage}</div>
              <div class="flex-1 flex items-center gap-3">
                <div class="flex-1 h-2 rounded-full bg-slate-800">
                  <div class="h-2 rounded-full bg-primary-600/70 transition-all" style={`width: ${s.bar}%`}></div>
                </div>
                <span class="w-8 text-right font-display text-sm font-semibold text-white">{s.n}</span>
              </div>
              <div class="hidden sm:block w-52 text-[10px] text-slate-600">{s.note}</div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── 4-Tier Scheme ─────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section id="tiers">
      <p class="section-label">Quality classification</p>
      <h2 class="section-title mb-3">4-Tier Scheme</h2>
      <p class="prose-aec mb-8 max-w-2xl">
        Every included benchmark is placed in exactly one tier based on thresholds applied to its
        10-dimension rubric score. <strong>Tier floors on d5, d6, d7</strong> (evaluation clarity,
        baseline coverage, reproducibility) are hard requirements for Tier 1 — these are the
        dimensions most predictive of result reusability.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        {[
          {
            tier: 'Tier 1',
            label: 'Core',
            count: '17',
            cls: 'border-emerald-800/60 bg-emerald-950/20',
            dot: 'bg-emerald-500',
            desc: 'Purpose-built for AEC tasks; primary objective is AEC AI evaluation; all d5/d6/d7 floors met.',
            floor: 'd5 ≥ 1, d6 ≥ 1, d7 ≥ 1 (evaluation clarity, baseline coverage, reproducibility — partial is sufficient)',
            examples: 'BuildArena (R001), DrafterBench (R005), HSE-Bench (R017), BIM-Edit (R031), CEQuest (R030)',
          },
          {
            tier: 'Tier 2',
            label: 'Peripheral',
            count: '6',
            cls: 'border-amber-800/60 bg-amber-950/20',
            dot: 'bg-amber-500',
            desc: 'AEC-relevant benchmarks that miss at least one d5/d6/d7 floor (floor dimension = 0) or whose primary scope is only partially AEC.',
            floor: 'At least one of d5/d6/d7 = 0, OR primary AEC scope is partial',
            examples: 'PE Civil Bench (R013), Construction Safety Poster Benchmark (R033), FloorplanQA (R011)',
          },
          {
            tier: 'Tier 3',
            label: 'Contextual',
            count: '1',
            cls: 'border-orange-800/60 bg-orange-950/20',
            dot: 'bg-orange-500',
            desc: 'AEC-relevant but adjacent — a training corpus or cross-domain resource with documented FM evidence of use, not a purpose-built AEC evaluation benchmark.',
            floor: 'Not a purpose-built evaluation benchmark; included as contextual resource only',
            examples: 'VL-Con (R023) — construction-site image training corpus (FM evidence: CLIP zero-shot probing)',
          },
        ].map(t => (
          <div class={`rounded-2xl border p-6 ${t.cls}`}>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <span class={`mt-1 h-3 w-3 rounded-full shrink-0 ${t.dot}`}></span>
              <div class="flex-1">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-1">
                  <h3 class="font-display text-base font-semibold text-white">{t.tier} — {t.label}</h3>
                  <span class="text-xs text-slate-500">({t.count} benchmarks)</span>
                </div>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-400 mb-2">{t.desc}</p>
                <div class="text-[11px] text-slate-600 mb-1">
                  <strong class="text-slate-500">Floor: </strong>{t.floor}
                </div>
                <div class="text-[11px] text-slate-600">
                  <strong class="text-slate-500">Examples: </strong>{t.examples}
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── 10-Dim Rubric ─────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section id="rubric">
      <p class="section-label">Scoring system</p>
      <h2 class="section-title mb-3">10-Dimension Rubric</h2>
      <p class="prose-aec mb-8 max-w-2xl">
        Each dimension is scored 0–2 by CURATOR extraction, following definitions grounded in
        the Datasheets for Datasets framework (Gebru et al., 2021), NeurIPS reproducibility
        checklist (Pineau et al., 2021), and AMSTAR-2 (Shea &amp; Reeves, 2017).
        Maximum total score: 20.
      </p>

      <div class="grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-2">
        {[
          { d: 'd1', name: 'Domain Authenticity',   desc: 'Data originates from real AEC projects or credible AEC-specific simulation; not repurposed general imagery.' },
          { d: 'd2', name: 'Task Validity',          desc: 'Benchmark tasks directly correspond to real AEC professional workflows or decision-making needs.' },
          { d: 'd3', name: 'Modality Coverage',      desc: 'Breadth of modalities covered (text, images, CAD, BIM, point cloud, etc.) relative to the stated AEC sub-domain.' },
          { d: 'd4', name: 'Annotation Quality',     desc: 'Ground-truth labels are precise, reviewed, inter-annotator agreement reported or annotation protocol described.' },
          { d: 'd5', name: 'Evaluation Clarity',     desc: 'Tier-1 floor (≥1): at least one primary metric defined and evaluation protocol described, even without public code. Full (=2): unambiguous metrics + per-class breakdowns + eval code or protocol public.' },
          { d: 'd6', name: 'Baseline Coverage',      desc: 'Tier-1 floor (≥1): at least one baseline result (human or model) reported with sufficient context for comparison. Full (=2): multiple baselines including a human-expert reference.' },
          { d: 'd7', name: 'Reproducibility',        desc: 'Floor (≥1 required for Tier 1 — NOT ≥2). 0 = no functioning public access pathway (author-on-request without URL, copyright-blocked, or release pending). 1 = partial pathway: code-only public, informal data link, or preprint-public [VERIFY]. 2 = full canonical release: data+code on stable repo (GitHub/HF/Zenodo) under open license.' },
          { d: 'd8', name: 'Leakage Control',        desc: 'Train/test splits are documented; leakage risks (e.g., pre-training overlap) are acknowledged or mitigated.' },
          { d: 'd9', name: 'Human Baseline',         desc: 'A credible human-performance reference point is reported, enabling calibration of model scores.' },
          { d: 'd10',name: 'Practical Relevance',    desc: 'Benchmark results map to actionable performance estimates for real deployments; not purely academic.' },
        ].map(dim => (
          <div class="rounded-xl bg-slate-900/60 border border-slate-800 px-4 py-3">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-1">
              <code class="font-mono text-[10px] text-primary-400 bg-primary-950/50 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">{dim.d}</code>
              <span class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-200">{dim.name}</span>
              {(dim.d === 'd5' || dim.d === 'd6' || dim.d === 'd7') && (
                <span class="text-[10px] text-emerald-500 font-medium" title="Tier 1 requires ≥1 on this dimension (partial is sufficient)">★ T1 ≥1</span>
              )}
            </div>
            <p class="text-[11px] text-slate-500 leading-relaxed">{dim.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── Provenance & Integrity ─────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section id="provenance">
      <p class="section-label">Data integrity</p>
      <h2 class="section-title mb-3">Provenance &amp; Integrity Philosophy</h2>
      <p class="prose-aec mb-8 max-w-2xl">
        AECplayground distinguishes between what is <em>reported by authors</em> and what has been
        <em>independently confirmed</em>. This distinction is surfaced on every record.
      </p>

      <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3 mb-10">
        {[
          {
            status: 'Source-Confirmed',
            badge: 'bg-primary-950/50 text-primary-300 border-primary-800/60',
            desc: 'Results have been verified against source files (raw logs, supplementary tables, or leaderboard APIs) by the VERIFIER agent.',
            note: 'Currently: HSE-Bench (R017) only — the single benchmark where source artifact verification was completed.',
          },
          {
            status: 'Claimed',
            badge: 'bg-slate-800/60 text-slate-400 border-slate-700/60',
            desc: 'Numbers are taken directly from the published paper\'s tables or abstract. No cross-checking against raw data or replication.',
            note: 'Most results in the catalog are in this state. Values should be treated as author-reported, not independently verified.',
          },
          {
            status: '[VERIFY] Pending',
            badge: 'bg-amber-950/50 text-amber-400 border-amber-800/60',
            desc: 'A number or identifier is present in the source but could not be confirmed from available artifacts. Requires VERIFIER resolution before catalog entry is finalized.',
            note: 'Example: R013 (PE Civil Bench) — paper title, dataset size, and performance figures require source confirmation from CACAIE proceedings (paywall). R033 (Construction Safety Poster Benchmark) has similar outstanding items.',
          },
        ].map(p => (
          <div class="rounded-2xl bg-slate-900/50 border border-slate-800 p-5">
            <span class={`chip text-xs border mb-3 ${p.badge}`}>{p.status}</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed mb-3">{p.desc}</p>
            <p class="text-[11px] text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">{p.note}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-2xl bg-amber-950/20 border border-amber-900/40 px-6 py-4">
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-700/90 leading-relaxed">
          <strong class="text-amber-500">No data is fabricated.</strong>
          Every number in this catalog traces to a specific CURATOR extraction or SYNTHESIZER aggregate.
          Records bearing <code class="font-mono text-amber-600">[VERIFY]</code> tags are visible to users
          but excluded from leaderboard comparisons until VERIFIER resolution.
          R032 is entirely excluded from the catalog per VERIFIER 0.5.23 finding F-054
          (framework-internal tool, no public release).
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── Literature grounding ─────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section id="references">
      <p class="section-label">Methodology grounding</p>
      <h2 class="section-title mb-6">Key Methodological References</h2>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        {[
          {
            key: 'Page2021',
            citation: 'Page MJ et al. (2021). "The PRISMA 2020 statement: an updated guideline for reporting systematic reviews." BMJ 372:n71.',
            role: 'PRISMA flow adapted for benchmark review context.',
          },
          {
            key: 'Gebru2021',
            citation: 'Gebru T et al. (2021). "Datasheets for Datasets." Communications of the ACM 64(12):86–92.',
            role: 'Informs d1–d4 (domain, task, modality, annotation) dimension definitions.',
          },
          {
            key: 'Pineau2021',
            citation: 'Pineau J et al. (2021). "Improving Reproducibility in Machine Learning Research." JMLR 22(164):1–20.',
            role: 'Informs d5, d7 (evaluation clarity, reproducibility) scoring criteria.',
          },
          {
            key: 'Kapoor2023',
            citation: 'Kapoor S & Narayanan A. (2023). "Leakage and the Reproducibility Crisis in Machine-Learning-based Science." Patterns 4(9).',
            role: 'Informs d8 (leakage control) dimension definition and scoring.',
          },
          {
            key: 'Shea2017',
            citation: 'Shea BJ & Reeves BC et al. (2017). "AMSTAR 2: a critical appraisal tool for systematic reviews." BMJ 358:j4008.',
            role: 'Quality appraisal framework adapted for AI benchmark systematic reviews.',
          },
          {
            key: 'Guyatt2008',
            citation: 'Guyatt GH et al. (2008). "GRADE: an emerging consensus on rating quality of evidence and strength of recommendations." BMJ 336:924.',
            role: 'Evidence-grading philosophy adapted for benchmark provenance classification.',
          },
          {
            key: 'Ravaut2025',
            citation: 'Ravaut M et al. (2025). "On the Evaluation of Machine Learning for Construction Safety." arXiv:2404.00699. Accepted TMLR 2025.',
            role: 'AEC-specific ML evaluation methodology reference for HSE/safety task design.',
          },
        ].map(ref => (
          <div class="flex gap-4 rounded-xl bg-slate-900/40 border border-slate-800 px-5 py-4">
            <code class="font-mono text-[10px] text-primary-400 shrink-0 mt-0.5">[{ref.key}]</code>
            <div>
              <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 leading-relaxed mb-1">{ref.citation}</p>
              <p class="text-[11px] text-slate-600">{ref.role}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── Agent System ──────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section id="system">
      <p class="section-label">How this catalog is built</p>
      <h2 class="section-title mb-3">The Agent Pipeline</h2>
      <p class="prose-aec mb-6 max-w-2xl">
        AECplayground is produced by a five-agent pipeline (DISCOVERER → CURATOR → SYNTHESIZER → CRAFTER → VERIFIER)
        orchestrated by a BOSS agent. Each agent has a bounded scope; no agent writes outside its own directory.
      </p>
      <div class="grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-5">
        {[
          { name: 'DISCOVERER', role: 'Search & identify candidate benchmarks across all three arms' },
          { name: 'CURATOR',    role: 'Extract structured records; apply 10-dim rubric; assign tier' },
          { name: 'SYNTHESIZER',role: 'Build taxonomy, performance maps, gap analysis, and future agenda' },
          { name: 'CRAFTER',    role: 'Write manuscript sections and build this living catalog' },
          { name: 'VERIFIER',   role: 'Resolve [VERIFY] tags; confirm identifiers, URLs, metrics' },
        ].map(a => (
          <div class="rounded-xl bg-slate-900/50 border border-slate-800 px-4 py-3">
            <div class="font-mono text-xs text-primary-300 font-semibold mb-1">{a.name}</div>
            <p class="text-[11px] text-slate-500 leading-relaxed">{a.role}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>
</Layout>
